parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause sudden loss of power, loss of control, and accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Transmission suddenly shifts from third to second gear
pieces of metal falling into the transmission pan

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the speedometer and odometer can cause difficulty in controlling the vehicle's speed, leading to accidents and near-misses.
symptoms: odometer does not work at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear axle failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: problem controlling the rear end of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended vehicle movement can cause accidents, loss of control, and damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: Vehicle jumps out of park into reverse gear
vehicle moves in driveway in park and idle position

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked or failed engine gaskets can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Failed engine mounts can cause vibration, noise, and engine damage, leading to reduced vehicle performance and potentially causing accidents.
Failed engine belts can cause engine damage, overheating, and loss of vehicle performance, potentially leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
Cracked or failed fuel lines can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
Power steering failure can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
Failed engine lifters can cause engine noise, vibration, and damage, leading to reduced vehicle performance and potentially causing accidents.
Intermittent stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
Oil leaks can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose braking action, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control.
symptoms: The brakes lock up and the vehicle slides
the pedal goes down and keeps moving
vehicle slides across crosswalk or highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor and does not stop the car

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control.
The failure of the brake rotor can cause extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control.
The noisy front brakes can be a sign of worn-out brake pads or other brake component failures, which can lead to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control if not addressed.
